    "Lloyd R. Bailey": "). This is in keeping with the priestly focus upon the father of the priesthood.\n14:5, \u201cfell on their faces.\u201d Such an action is usually a prelude to worship of God or subordination to a superior, but here\nresults from despair and grief (as at 16:4).\n14:9, \u201cbread for us.\u201d A unique expression, meaning that we will be able to consume (defeat) them.\n[v_Exo_32_10] 14:12, \u201cA nation . . . greater than they.\u201d God\u2019s ultimate threat, echoing Exod 32:",
